@FBuckley17 @pmbairrins @MichaelMDowling @ItaOKelly @BarbaraMcMahon8 @gazzahead Tell me about it!

I'm mid 50's and hold a Master's Degree. I have had 5 interviews in 3 years, and didn't get beyond that!

I'm not even applying for 'high flying' jobs! I'm going for anything and everything.The same companies that turn me down are advertising again weeks later.

@TinaMur79949519 @MichaelMDowling @BarbaraMcMahon8 @gazzahead True.
A huge waste of talent and experience.
I imagine forced retirement must be traumatic for many with lively enquiring minds and good health on their side.

@BarbaraMcMahon8 @gazzahead Yes it is a difficult and very rigid system.
What I have learned is that many people do not ultimately work in the field they studied in. 
So perhaps the area you choose doesn't actually matter that much!
